  "instructions": [
    "Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat. Add namul-blanch-season and whisk to combine. Add Reblochon cheese, a slice at a time, whisking until smooth and melted. Add beef broth, whisk until combined. Bring to a simmer and cook until heated through. Fry french fries in cold-pressed canola oil until crispy. Drain fries on paper towels. In a large serving dish, spread a layer of fries. Pour Reblochon sauce over fries. Top with additional fries and chopped chives, if using."
